THOUGHT: The wrong transformation comes from SCCPSolver using ConstantFoldInstOperands, which can fold fcmp with constants without considering the function’s denormal-fp-math being "ieee,dynamic". To fix, I will modify SCCPSolver.cpp to avoid constant-folding floating-point compare instructions when the enclosing function has dynamic denormal mode. I’ll insert a guard before calling ConstantFoldInstOperands: if the instruction is an FCmp and the type is floating-point (including vector of FP) and the parent function’s DenormalMode has Input or Output as Dynamic, then skip folding. This prevents collapsing a lane-wise compare into a splat under dynamic denormals.

```bash
applypatch << 'EOF'
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp
@@
   if (Constant *C = ConstantFoldInstOperands(&I, Operands, DL))
     return C;
+
+  // Avoid constant-folding floating-point comparisons under dynamic denormal mode.
+  // IPSCCP should respect "denormal-fp-math"="ieee,dynamic" because denormal handling
+  // can affect the result of comparisons, especially for vectors with non-splat
+  // constants. Folding may incorrectly assume IEEE behavior and produce wrong results.
+  // Guard FCmp from folding when the parent function has dynamic denormal configuration.
+  if (I.getOpcode() == Instruction::FCmp) {
+    auto *Ty = I.getType();
+    auto IsFPOrFPVector = [](Type *T) {
+      if (T->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
+        return true;
+      // isFPOrFPVectorTy covers both scalar FP and FP vectors in recent LLVM.
+      // For compatibility, also check explicitly:
+      if (T->isVectorTy())
+        return T->getScalarType()->isFloatingPointTy();
+      return T->isFloatingPointTy();
+    };
+    if (IsFPOrFPVector(Ty)) {
+      const Function *F = I.getFunction();
+      if (F) {
+        // Use the semantics of the compared operands if vector/scalar FP.
+        // Query on double semantics is conservative enough to catch dynamic.
+        DenormalMode Mode = F->getDenormalMode(APFloat::IEEEdouble());
+        if (Mode.Input == DenormalMode::Dynamic || Mode.Output == DenormalMode::Dynamic) {
+          // Do not fold FCmp under dynamic denormals.
+          return nullptr;
+        }
+      }
+    }
+  }
*** End Patch
EOF
```

